post_text: Did you know that there is a new Accredited Performing Arts private school for dancers? It‚Äôs called Academy 7 in Pleasant Grove! They work with your high school to receive credit for dance classes. Academy 7 also follows Alpine School District A/B schedule which allows you to take dance classes and train for high school credit in the morning and take your academic classes at your high school that you are currently attending. Academy 7 is having an open house on May 20th to answer any questions that you may have and give you a tour. See details below!

post_text:
Attention to Our PHSPA Community at Large!!!

Following the announcement of our school‚Äôs closure, a special event was announced at our open house on August 6th, and now it‚Äôs happening! Our official PHSPA ‚ÄúElysium Funeral Party‚Äù is going to be held next Saturday, September 1st, from 7-10 PM at the Utah Military Academy, 3901 W. Waterbury Dr, Lehi, UT. Below is a link to the Facebook page for this event.

Please plan to come, and please help spread the word to everyone you know in the Pioneer community!! We want everyone to be there!

This farewell event has been generously organized by Brandon Hanks, a former student body president, and will include performances from several students and teachers across the short life of our school, from 2013-2018.

There is also a pot-luck dessert happening, so don‚Äôt forget to bring your favorite treat to share!

I hope to see you ALL there!

Dallyn Vail Bayles
Executive Director
Pioneer High School for the Performing Arts

post_text: We are excited to announce our new Executive Director, Dallyn Bayles! Dallyn comes with an impressive resume which includes the Phantom and Raoul in the touring company of The Phantom of the Opera, Enjolras in the touring company of Les Miserables as well as a distinguished solo career appearing in front of The Mormon Tabernacle Choir, alongside Colm Wilkinson, Kurt Bestor and other high profile events. We are thrilled to have his performative leadership at the helm of Pioneer! The future looks bright! For more information, visit pioneercharterschool.org #pioneerhighschoolfortheperformingarts #dallynvailbayles #performingarts #utahtheatre #utahschools

Save the Date: Oct. 17th. Musical theatre master class with guest artist Dallyn Bayles. One of the many great opportunities for students at a charter school for the performing arts.

"I Hope I Get It!"
Broadway touring musical theatre and vocal recording sensation Dallyn Bayles will conduct a master class teaching students the do's and don'ts of choosing, preparing, and performing a killer musical theatre audition. PHS Alumni Feature
Monica Smith attended Pioneer High School and graduated with a 4.0 and is attending BYU on a talent scholarship, majoring in MDT. She starred in the recent motion picture "Saturday‚Äôs Warrior" as Julie Flinders, acted in the viral Mormon Message Bullying - Stop It, was the lead in a new church video series "Seeking Fairness for All", and worked in many other films and commercials. She has performed on the stages of Hale, Sundance, and Lincoln Center in NYC. On top of all this she is creating her own content and in production for her own music video.

post_text:
Meet Kylee - An Example of PHS Talent:
Kylee started attending Pioneer High school her freshman year when the school had just opened. She first heard of Odyssey Dance Theater through the school, she had the opportunity to work with Derryl Yeager in doing a variation of the dying swan solo from Swan Lake which she performed in the first Best of PHS showcase. In 11th grade she was given an internship to perform with Odyssey Dance Theater in their Christmas show, The Redux Nutcracker. Then Kylee‚Äôs senior year she started dancing with Odyssey Dance Theater professionally where she had the opportunity to perform in all five of their productions, and travel with them to Germany on their Europe tour.
text:
Meet Kylee - An Example of PHS Talent:
Kylee started attending Pioneer High school her freshman year when the school had just opened. She first heard of Odyssey Dance Theater through the school, she had the opportunity to work with Derryl Yeager in doing a variation of the dying swan solo from Swan Lake which she performed in the first Best of PHS showcase. In 11th grade she was given an internship to perform with Odyssey Dance Theater in their Christmas show, The Redux Nutcracker. Then Kylee‚Äôs senior year she started dancing with Odyssey Dance Theater professionally where she had the opportunity to perform in all five of their productions, and travel with them to Germany on their Europe tour.

post_text:
Pioneer High School is proud to announce a new opportunity for our students! This June, we will be taking students to Washington D.C. Students will tour sites such as:
- Lincoln, Jefferson, Korea, Vietnam, and WWII memorials
- Arlington National Cemetery
- Smithsonian Museums (Air and Space, American History, Natural History and National Art)
- U.S. Capitol Building
- Gettysburg, Pennsylvania
- Fort McHenry
- Harpers Ferry, West Virginia
We will also be going to a Baltimore Orioles vs. New York Yankees baseball game!
The trip will be 6 days, 5 nights, beginning on June 3rd. This is a great educational experience and costs less than $1,200. Come connect with history in our nations capital! Space is limited. A $100 deposit is required by October 14th to secure your place on the trip. For more information or to reserve your spot, contact me at sarah.nielsen@pioneercharterschool.org or 801-768-8787. This trip is going to be amazing!!!

Hello PHS!

It's a pleasure to post here informing you of the PHS Student Council election results. We look forward to these great leaders stepping up next year to make a fantastic contribution!

Student Body President: Whitney Wilson
Student Body Vice President: Makai Black
Dance Academy Representative: Anna Morales
Music Academy Representative: Justin Painter
Theater Academy Representative: Jordan Flores

We will be appointing a 9th grade senator, a 10th grade senator, and an 11th grade senator at a future date. Congratulations to the elected positions listed above.

Thanks, Olympians, for all you do for our school!
text:
Hello PHS!

It's a pleasure to post here informing you of the PHS Student Council election results. We look forward to these great leaders stepping up next year to make a fantastic contribution!

Student Body President: Whitney Wilson
Student Body Vice President: Makai Black
Dance Academy Representative: Anna Morales
Music Academy Representative: Justin Painter
Theater Academy Representative: Jordan Flores

We will be appointing a 9th grade senator, a 10th grade senator, and an 11th grade senator at a future date. Congratulations to the elected positions listed above.

Thanks, Olympians, for all you do for our school!

post_text: Hello all! Here's a quick reminder that this Saturday at 8:00pm, students who want to do individual or group numbers for the Best of PHS show (coming up on May 13. Mark your calendars!) should plan to bring their number (whether it be a monologue, solo or group musical number, or scene) to the Open mic night in studio 6 to audition! Come one, come all. It should be a great evening all by itself, but it will be especially useful for you as an audition for Best of PHS!

post_text: Hey PHS! Every month (usually on the third Saturday of the month), the COPA building hosts an open mic night. Whether your a singer or an instrumentalist, a solo act or a member of a band, it's a great opportunity to perform, and hone your chops before an audience. It's free to perform or attend. The next open mic night lasts from 8-10pm, on December 20th.

Who's pumped for Thanksgiving?! The Student Council is! So, in order to bring more Thanksgiving fun to Pioneer, we are announcing our THANKSGIVING UGLY SWEATER STOMP! Woohoo! There will be a contest with prizes for the ugliest sweater.

Friday, November 21st. 8-11 PM. In the Black Box.
Entrance will be $2 or 2 cans of food.
We will be donating any cans given to the Utah Food Bank to fight hunger in Utah this holiday season. Come support your school and the Utah Food Bank! And wear the ugliest sweater you can get your hands on! Hope to see you there! (:

post_text:
Hey all!

Monday is a busy day at Pioneer. First of all, ALL SENIORS (and any juniors who at graduating this year) need to be at the school at 7:50am on Monday. The bus is taking seniors to American Fork High School that hour for college day. You'll be there from 8:00am to 11:30. Then the bus will bring you back.

Now. Normally seniors would be done with school by then, and on their way home. But if you're a senior in the MUSIC ACADEMY, please arrange to come back to the COPA building for a fantastic guest presentation from one of the great drummers and music educators, Daniel Glass. This is going to be hugely cool. Here's a video to give you a sense of the coolness. Mr. Glass will be presenting to the juniors during 2nd hour (9:25-10:45), and the freshmen, sophomores, and seniors during third hour (11:35-1:00).

So, yeah, busy day on Monday. Busy, awesome day.

Best,

Sam

post_text:
Our assembly today kicked off "Homecoming Week!" We have fun activities, dress-up days, and contests all week long. Homecoming Week concludes on Saturday with our Homecoming Dance. We hope everyone is planning on coming!

Schedule for the week:
Monday: scavenger hunt begins, hand in papers at front desk before school on Friday for a chance to win free Homecoming tickets
Tuesday: Selfie Day-post one thing you have in common with hashtag #PHSselfie, prize for most and best posts
Wednesday: Performing Arts Hero Day, find out who people admire, exchange names, and play the candy game! To play get papers from student council members on Tuesday.
Thursday: School Colors Day, Positive Day, (play the candy game-post 5 great things about PHS), Pay People Compliments Day, Powder Puff Football 3:00
Friday: Pajama and Pirate Day
Saturday: Homecoming Dance in The Black Box (Disney Theme-dress up and receive $2 off your ticket)

post_text:
Hello all! Derryl Yeager sent me an email yesterday that included a message for our grads. Here it is:

Dear PHS Graduating Students, Teachers, and Family Members -
I sincerely apologize for not being able to attend the Graduation Ceremony today! My duties at Tuacahn in staging The Little Mermaid have made it impossible to get away this weekend as we finish the final preparations for opening the show this Saturday. Please know that my heart is with you all this day! Pioneer High School for the Performing Arts has been a 25-year dream of mine - and today as we graduate our second group of seniors, I am still amazed at the fact that we are here now - living this dream! Starting a school from scratch has been filled with many challenges and issues that have taxed all those involved to the limit - but those challenges have been made worthwhile by the Students and Families that have taken the chance with us! I thank you and honor you ALL this day - you have been the true ‚ÄúPioneers‚Äù of Pioneer High! May your dreams come true too!
All the best and congratulations!

Derryl Yeager

Hello Olympians!

After a terrific assembly this morning, we're ready to announce the 2014-2015 PHS Student Council. We're very proud of all the students who ran, and want to express our love and appreciation to all of them for making PHS what it is! Here's the list (drum roll please):

Student Body President: Chandler Willey
Student Body Vice President: Jared Butler
Dance Academy Representative: Lauren Hansen
Music Academy Representative: Colton Wheat
Musical Theater Representative: Alessia Love
Activities Representative: Whitney Wilson

We're looking forward to a wonderful year in 2014-2015, with great student leaders.

Best,

Sam Payne
School Director

Time to post another bio from one of our terrific Bye Bye Birdie actors! Come see her and the rest of the gang in the play in the Lehi Jr. High School Auditorium on Friday and Saturday. Heck, see the show three times! Tickets are available at the front desk, and at the door. Here's a bit about Shayna Larsen (with many thanks for delivering these bios to us):

Shayna has enjoyed acting from a young age. Whether it was acting older so she could get into certain movies, or ‚Äúacting‚Äù like the other kid broke their own arm, what Shayna has can be described as no less than a natural talent for the thing. She‚Äôd like to thank her mentors, who you can ask her all about (and include everyone from her great PHS teachers to Ian Ellis to...um...communist dictators for some reason), for helping make her the person she is today.

post_text:
Oh, what the heck. We'll post two bios today : )

This is JARED BUTLER! Come see him this weekend, on Friday and Saturday, in Bye Bye Birdie! Here's a bit from his bio:

"Jared Butler would like to thank his parents for putting up with his long hair and constant off pitch singing while being in this show. A special thanks goes out to his best friends, Carleigh and Chandler who have always been there to provide a much needed hug, kick in the pants, or a flamboyant comment. While he loves musical theatre, he is a ballet boy at heart. When he isn't prancing around on stage in tights he enjoys cooking, playing guitar, shopping, hanging out with his best friends, and trying to catch 'em all. For Narnia!"

Super excited to see Jared and the gang take the stage in awesome style this weekend!

Bye Bye Birdie is coming up this weekend! So excited to see all the hard work pay off under the lights. As a teaser, we want to post the bios and photos of some of the cast members. We'll start off with the remarkable ALESSIA LOVE! Here's a bit from her bio (with special thanks to Shayna Larsen, who collected the bios and photos for us).

"Alessia Love is thrilled to be a part of Bye Bye Birdie. She loves musicals and the 50s and super hot rock stars, and that's pretty much what BBB is about, so that's good. Also, she would like to thank all those that put work into the show, because so many people did and they all rock. P.S. You are enough, you are so enough, it's unbelievable how enough you are!"

Watch this space for more photos and bios from the terrific cast of Bye Bye Birdie, and come see the show this Friday and Saturday in the Lehi Jr. High Auditorium!

post_text: Hey Olympians! REMINDER: Prom is this Saturday! It is going to sooooo fun. There will be a live band, a photo booth, and possibly some snacks! Its being held at Velour, one of Utah's premier indie venues. So don't miss it!! Single tickets are $15. Couples are $25. And a group of 5 students is $50. DATES ARE NOT REQUIRED!!! Its more of a dance party than a formal dance! So come and bring your friends!! See you all then!! :D

post_text: You heard it at the Gold and Scold, but here it is again: on Friday the 14th at 7:30 PM, the black box will be transformed into a theatre where we will be showing Austenland and providing plenty of snacks for your pleasure. post_text: Valograms will be ready to order tomorrow! For 3$, you can sign up to send a special valentine to anyone you'd like. Pay Carol at the front desk to receive a card. Please put the receiver's name on the card somewhere; anonymous valograms are just fine, but valograms without recipients can't be sent. Give the card back to Carol and all valograms will be delivered on Valentine's DAy!
